					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250852" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;" >djkaktus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1413159280 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Oct 2014 00:14</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2130370">
									

<p>I thought about those things. Here's what I decided on, at the end.</p>
<p>1.) He can't look in on her. The Scarlet King is weak until he's born, and is only able to interact with the Foundationverse by &quot;feeling through the air&quot;, so to speak. If he was actually strong enough, don't you think he'd just be able to appear himself wherever he wanted, and completely forego being born? He can't do that, though (for whatever reason), and has to rely on the actions of the Children of the Scarlet King to bring him into the world. Even in each of the previous iterations, he couldn't even handle the Foundation. If he was truly a powerful ethereal entity, don't you think the Foundation would be nothing before him?</p>
<p>2.) You're going to have to take my word for it, basically. There's such a strong tide of emotion conveyed about the nature of 231, much of which has been implanted and manipulated by the Foundation itself, that a few researchers aren't going to leave an impression on him. I speak again to the first point here as well; in this weakened state, he can't differentiate between what the researchers are feeling, and what literally everybody else is feeling. It's all a wash to him, and that's why he hasn't been able to awaken.</p>
<p>As for why he doesn't react to the little girl, hers is the only intellect that he has direct access to. If he feels fear from so many other people, and then feels something from her (even if it's happiness, and better if it's joy (since that's a stronger emotion)), he believes that fear is what she's feeling.</p>
<p>To simplify, to Scarlet King can smell fear. The Scarlet King does not know that fear feels like. The Scarlet King does know that there is both fear, and an emotion coming from her. Thus, the Scarlet King believes that she is feeling fear.</p>
<p>I know a lot of this looks like handwaving, and I understand if that's what you think. But what it boils down to is that the Scarlet King, weakened as he is, cannot tell the difference between actual fear and fabricated fear, and cannot tell the difference between actual terrible acts and only simulated terrible acts. Because of this, he believes he is still bound by the old laws, and remains dormant.</p>

							</div>

								
					
