<p>2) It actually isn't too much of a handwave.<br />
It's literally how conspiracy theories and superstitions live in the world - people taking in the opinion of an unqualified mass over the opinions of people who understand what's going on.<br />
If the demon can't distinguish, and well, he feels the minds of the hundreds of employees with tacit or expressed thoughts about the procedure and quiet dread they'll be assigned to it, versus the three-four who at any time know what's going on, which seems like the more plausible variant to it?</p>
<p>In related note, after a good bit of deliberation, I decided to give this one an upvote after all, despite my headcanon saying whale, and despite Lucavex Anayami (?) coming up with a better tale ages ago.<br />
Pity it wasn't a shadowcast of Rocky Horror Picture Show though - that the old site FAQ was literally true would have been a nice cherry on the cake.</p>

