<blockquote>
<p>How has the King never looked in specifically to see how horrible she has it? I can't buy someone who is more or less the Sauron of the Skip'verse /not/ actually checking in and just taking a bunch of mortal emotions and reactions at face value, much less not be able to feel the girl's own emotions to see that she's not actually living a real life nightmare.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Well, if he does, the Foundation can always revert to the previous Montauk procedure for a while, until big bad daddy sleeps again. Who says it hasn't happened before? Amnestics, you know.</p>
<p>I love this. I love everything about it. Genius development from SCP-231, excellent writing, and a very excellent reply from Djkaktus to Vincent Redgrave's post. I'm also very happy to know that Dr Clef approves of this.<br />
I don't feel so guilty about SCP-231 being my favourite now!</p>
<p>And sorry for the necropost, had to speak up&#8230;</p>

